efault&amp;leRepAvState=3&amp;referrer=(button%20dynamic-button:Email%20button_default(Email%20Settings%20for%20on-%20and%20off-campus%20Connections))%20http%3A//www.byui.edu/information-technology/services-and-systems/email-for-employees/setup">Need help with your email?<br />Click here to chat with an expert or leave us a message after hours.</a></h3>
<p>The best configuration for Student email for mobile devices is to use the "Exchange" setting.&nbsp;For help configuring your devices for e-mail, you may use one of these tutorials:</p>
<p>For iPod or iPad instructions click <a href="http://www.byui.edu/help-desk/imobile-device-configuration-(student)">here</a>.</p>
<p>For Android instructions click&nbsp;<a class="intLink" href="x90302.xml" title="Android Email Setup">here</a>.</p>
<p>If you already have an email account set up on your Android device you can add another by following these steps:</p>
<ol type="1">
<li>Go to you "Email" app</li>
<li>Press the option button below your phone's screen</li>
<li>From this menu select "Account Settings"</li>
<li>Press the "+" symbol at the top of the screen to add a new account</li>
<li>Once you get to this screen follow the instructions <a href="http://www.byui.edu/help-desk/android-first-time-configuration-(student)">here</a>&nbsp;(skipping steps 1 and 2)</li>
</ol>
<p>If this does not work or options are not available on your phone you can also try the tutorial <a href="http://www.byui.edu/help-desk/android-multi-email-configuration-(student)">here</a>.</p>
<p>For Microsoft's indepth guide to setting up your mobile device <a href="http://help.outlook.com/en-US/140/Dd936215.aspx">go here</a></p>]]></BodyCopy><xPower Type="GroupStart" GroupStart="" Name="PageComponents" label="Page Components" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Expanded=""><xPower Type="List" List="xpowercomponent_Optional" Name="OptionalColumnComponent" label="Optional Column Components" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" Component="" CompTypes="FacebookComponent;Image;ColumnTextComponent;Media;Quote" Expanded="false"><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="Optional" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="FacebookComponent;Image;ColumnTextComponent;Media;Quote" Expanded="false"/></xPower><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="QuickLinksColumn1" label="QuickLinks Column 1" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="QuickLinksComponent"/><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="QuickLinksColumn2" label="QuickLinks Column 2" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="QuickLinksComponent"/><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="QuickLinksColumn3" label="QuickLinks Column 3" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="QuickLinksComponent"/></xPower><xPower Type="Component" Component="" Name="HighlightedLinks" label="Highlighted Links" readonly="false" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="HighlightedLinksComponent" Expanded="false"/><xPower Type="Navigation" StartPage="x5" MaxDepth="" MaxNodes="" GenerationOrder="down" Navigation="Ancestors" Query="" Name="AncestorNavigation" label="Ancestor Navigation" readonly="true" hidden="true" required="false" Expanded="false"/><xPower Type="Component" Component="x35726" Name="SiteControl" label="Site Control" readonly="true" hidden="false" required="false" CompTypes="SiteControl" Expanded="false"/></Content>
